text: Prairie rattlesnake may refer to: * Crotalus viridis, a.k.a. the plains rattlesnake, a venomous pitviper species native to the western United States, southwestern Canada, and northern Mexico. * Sistrurus catenatus, a.k.a. the massassauga, a venomous pitviper species found primarily in the United States.
title: Prairie rattlesnake
